<p><strong>Airport Shuttles</strong></p>
<p>The Public Relations Office provides an Internet listing of commercial  shuttle and bus service providers to and from the Salt Lake City and  Idaho Falls airports. See <a href="http://www.byui.edu/pr/studenttravel/default.htm" target="_parent">http://www.byui.edu/pr/studenttravel/default.htm</a></p>
<p><strong>Driving Directions</strong></p>
<p><strong>•Heading south on I-15</strong></p>
<p>Exit I-15 at Sage Junction onto US-33 which brings you directly into  Main Street of Rexburg (see Area Map). Approximate distance 21 miles.  From Main Street, campus is two blocks south, best reached by heading  south on either 2nd West or 2nd East.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>•Heading north on I-15</strong></p>
<p>Exit I-15 at Idaho Falls Exit 119 onto US-20, heading towards Rigby and  West Yellowstone. (see Area Map) After approximately 25 miles, exit  US-20 at the South Rexburg/BYU-Idaho exit and turn right. After crossing  the railroad tracks, continue through the light on University Boulevard  until in intersects with 7th South at the southwest corner of campus.*  (see Local Map)</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>Optional route:</em> After crossing the railroad tracks, turn left  at the light onto W. Yellowstone Highway. Directional signs to BYU-Idaho  will guide you to 7th South where you will turn right to reach campus.  Or you can stay on the Yellowstone Highway but continue going east onto  Viking Drive (4th South) at intersection of 2nd West.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>•From the Idaho Falls Airport</strong></p>
<p>As you exit the Idaho Falls Airport, you need to turn left at the first  stop light which puts you directly onto US-20. (see above instructions).</p>
<p>The BYU-Idaho Testing Center in Rexburg Idaho is located in the Manwaring Center.</p>
<p><strong>Restaurants and Lodging</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rexcc.com" target="_blank">Rexburg Chamber of Commerce</a> provides a listing of local restaurants and lodging facilities.</p>
<p> </p>
